DIGEST
SB 199 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Seabaugh
Present law provides that for a 2nd offense of purchasing commercial sexual activity, an
offender be fined not less than $1,500 nor more than $2,000, imprisoned, with or without
hard labor, for not more than two years, or both, and that one-half of the fines collected be
distributed in accordance with present law.
Proposed law requires an offender to register as a sex offender and imposes a mandatory
term of imprisonment of between six months and two years without benefit of probation,
parole, or suspension of sentence.
Proposed law otherwise retains present law.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 14:82.2(C)(2))
